span.p:
Theorem 8.1
For a p-by-n matrix, rows are linearly independent if and only if there exists a p-by-p submatrix whose determinant is nonzero.

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Theorem 8.2
Rank of a matrix equals the number of rows of the largest square submatrix in it whose determinant is nonzero.

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Corollary 8.3
Rank of a n-by-n matrix has rank n if and only if its determinant is nonzero.

span.p:
Theorem 8.4
Interchanging two adjacent elements in a permutation changes its sign.

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: normal; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;
display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Theorem 8.5
Property (1) of Determinants
Interchanging a row in square matrix A changes the sign of the determinant.

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Theorem 8.6
Property (3) of Determinants
Replacing a row in square matrix A with the sum of this row and a multiple of another row will not change the determinant.

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Theorem 8.7
The determinant of a square matrix in triangular form is the product of the elements along its diagonal.

span.p:
Theorem 7.1
Rank(coefficient matrix) = dim(range space).

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Corollary 7.2
If rank < number of equations, there exists b for which Ax = b has no solutions. If rank = number of equations, range space is Vn.

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: normal; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p:
Corollary 7.3
Col rank = row rank.

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Theorem 7.4
Solutions to general linear system = a particular solution + solutions to the homogeneous system.

Rank(coefficient matrix)

Dual Theorem 4.4
Any spanning sets of dimension number of vectors are linearly independent.

linear independence
no vector is a linear combination of others (exception: set of zero vector is not considered independent)

An equivalent condition for linear independence.

span.p:
Corollary 4.2
A set of linearly independent vectors joined with a vector outside its spanned subspace is still linearly independent.

Any independent sets in a subspace can have no more vectors than do any spanning sets in that subspace.
